<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5592&amp;p=50882#p50882"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[60pin to 72pin converter]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5592&amp;p=50882#p50882"><![CDATA[
If the board you have has a 60 pin edge connector (for Famicom) you need an adapter to plug it into and the other end of the adapter should have a 72 pin edge connector to go into the NES. <br /><br />A pirate/clone NES does not have a lockout chip AT ALL. The board with the 500-in-1 has no lockout chip either. There is no need for it. <br /><br />Really all you are really asking is how do I play a Famicom cartridge on my NES. It's simple, you need an adapter.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1726">MottZilla</a> — Mon Sep 28, 2009 3:46 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
